description.narrative: 1. Screening: deliver a robust portfolio of early hits and lead series to enable drug discovery for Chagas disease 2. Hit-to-lead: identify new leads with activity in animal models of disease and the potential for further optimization 3. Identify and evaluate new biological markers of therapeutic efficacy in chronic Chagas disease 4. Deliver a new regimen of benznidazole in monotherapy and/or in combination with Fosravuconazole 5. Evaluate efficacy and safety of short-cours and low-dose regimens of fexinidazole in adults with chronic Chagas disease 6. Chagas access project: demonstrate the feasibility of scaling up access to diagnosis and treatment in pilot projects that can be replicated on a larger scale"

DNDi aims to deliver new safer more affordable and effective treatments for people affected by Chagas disease. DNDi is also focused on improving access to diagnosis and treatment using existing tools.
